text: Tsogkhuugiin Udval (; born 18 August 1994) is a Mongolian female ju-jitsu practitioner. She represented Mongolia at the 2018 Asian Games and claimed a bronze medal in the women's 62kg ne-waza event. == References == Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Mongolian female martial artists Category:Ju-jitsu practitioners at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Asian Games bronze medalists for Mongolia Category:Asian Games medalists in ju-jitsu
